113
00:06:39.524 --> 00:06:41.442
Oh. no. Let's go. champ! Come on.

114
00:06:42.735 --> 00:06:45.988
[Colom] <i>When Toni and Rafael trained.</i>

115
00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:50.076
{\an8}tensions were very high.

116
00:06:51.452 --> 00:06:53.454
[Toni] Rafael. don't hit it so low.

117
00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:56.666
"Rafa. turn around."
"Rafa. move." "Rafa. finish the shot"â€¦

118
00:06:56.749 --> 00:06:57.708
From ball one.

119
00:06:58.751 --> 00:07:00.545
<i>He was constantly correcting him.</i>

120
00:07:01.337 --> 00:07:04.424
<i>Trying to create</i>
<i>the maximum amount of stress.</i>

121
00:07:04.507 --> 00:07:05.925
Again! Come on!

122
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:09.595
I felt much less pressure
when playing against any opponent

123
00:07:09.679 --> 00:07:11.264
than when training with Toni.

124
00:07:12.723 --> 00:07:13.641
[Toni] Again!

125
00:07:13.724 --> 00:07:15.351
When I missed a ball. he'd ask.

126
00:07:16.144 --> 00:07:17.270
"Why did you miss?"

127
00:07:17.353 --> 00:07:21.858
I was scared of making another mistake.

128
00:07:23.151 --> 00:07:27.071
During the first hour of training.
no water.

129
00:07:27.655 --> 00:07:29.282
One hour without drinking.

130
00:07:29.782 --> 00:07:33.119
So. they would learn to suffer a little.

131
00:07:34.370 --> 00:07:38.082
Some coaches rebelled against me

132
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.168
because they felt that was barbaric.

133
00:07:42.253 --> 00:07:44.881
I remember.
in the first round of a tournament.

134
00:07:45.506 --> 00:07:47.758
I fell and broke this finger.

135
00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:52.597
[Toni] <i>When this happened to his finger.</i>
<i>I told Rafael. "Keep playing."</i>

136
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:54.807
<i>"Play for as long as you can."</i>

137
00:07:59.187 --> 00:08:04.233
I won the tournament.
But I had to wear a cast for a month.

138
00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:11.991
{\an8}If you had asked me at that time.
"Do you agree with all this?"

139
00:08:12.074 --> 00:08:15.328
I would have said. "No. I don't like it."

140
00:08:16.412 --> 00:08:18.164
<i>It was a philosophy.</i>

141
00:08:18.247 --> 00:08:20.666
<i>"Learn how to suffer through a sport."</i>

142
00:08:21.918 --> 00:08:26.714
I always said the same thing to him.
"Rafa. you don't have to play."

143
00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:30.384
"No. I'm fine. Mom.
I really like doing this."

144
00:08:31.010 --> 00:08:32.053
Last one.

145
00:08:33.137 --> 00:08:36.974
I only remember one time
I felt like I couldn't take it anymore.

146
00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:41.270
and said. "Toni. umâ€¦
I'm sorry. but I can't go on."

147
00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:44.815
<i>I left the court.</i>

148
00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:48.736
<i>Mentally destroyed and crying.</i>

149
00:08:52.156 --> 00:08:54.992
<i>But I never went home crying.</i>

150
00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:57.203
My father would ask. "How was practice?"

151
00:08:57.286 --> 00:08:58.788
I'd say. "Fine. good."

152
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:00.164
"Bad."

153
00:09:01.082 --> 00:09:02.041
But that was it.

154
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:07.463
<i>I never would have wanted</i>
<i>for my dad to go up to Toni</i>

155
00:09:08.047 --> 00:09:10.091
<i>and ask him to go easy on me.</i>

156
00:09:10.883 --> 00:09:14.971
<i>I would have felt</i>
<i>like I was letting Toni down.</i>

157
00:09:15.471 --> 00:09:19.308
I'd be a person
who wasn't strong enough to endure.

158
00:09:20.726 --> 00:09:23.938
<i>I always knew</i>
<i>that he wanted the best for me.</i>

159
00:09:24.438 --> 00:09:26.691
<i>He wanted to make me succeed.</i>

160
00:09:27.191 --> 00:09:30.027
And he believed that the right way wasâ€¦

161
00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:33.114
that one.

162
00:09:33.197 --> 00:09:34.615
[inspirational music playing]

163
00:09:35.575 --> 00:09:36.909
<i>Pushing me to the limit.</i>

164
00:09:41.539 --> 00:09:42.707
[commentator] <i>He's done it!</i>

165
00:09:46.627 --> 00:09:50.089
[Toni] <i>I am not satisfied</i>
<i>with him being a good player.</i>

166
00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:56.762
