<i>Because every point counts.</i>

652
00:39:44.090 --> 00:39:46.884
[commentator] <i>Here we go.</i>
<i>Fourth set tie-break.</i>

653
00:39:50.179 --> 00:39:51.389
[tense music playing]

654
00:39:53.516 --> 00:39:54.517
[fan] Come on!

655
00:40:00.856 --> 00:40:02.024
[cheering erupts]

656
00:40:02.108 --> 00:40:05.069
[commentator] <i>If all seven points</i>
<i>in the breaker are gonna be like that.</i>

657
00:40:05.152 --> 00:40:06.821
<i>the crowd are gonna lose their voices.</i>

658
00:40:08.030 --> 00:40:10.282
There were multiple moments
when they played.

659
00:40:10.366 --> 00:40:12.118
"Anything you can do. I can do better."

660
00:40:19.792 --> 00:40:21.001
[umpire] One all.

661
00:40:21.502 --> 00:40:23.921
They both deeply believed
it was their match to win.

662
00:40:24.964 --> 00:40:26.382
[umpire] Two-one.

663
00:40:26.465 --> 00:40:27.550
Three-one.

664
00:40:28.300 --> 00:40:29.718
Four-one.

665
00:40:29.802 --> 00:40:32.179
Four-two. Nadal.

666
00:40:33.889 --> 00:40:37.893
[commentator] <i>That's wide!</i>
<i>And that could be the crucial blow!</i>

667
00:40:37.977 --> 00:40:41.939
[laughs] <i>Uncle Toni</i>
<i>can't even watch anymore.</i>

668
00:40:42.022 --> 00:40:43.399
[umpire] Five-two. Nadal.

669
00:40:43.482 --> 00:40:47.778
[commentator] <i>He's coached this young man</i>
<i>since he was four years old.</i>

670
00:40:48.904 --> 00:40:52.116
[Toni] <i>Serving. the pressure is on him.</i>

671
00:40:53.075 --> 00:40:57.830
Because 5-2 in the tie-break
of the fourth is almost a victory.

672
00:41:00.624 --> 00:41:01.667
[line] Fault!

673
00:41:02.710 --> 00:41:03.752
[Toni] <i>Fault.</i>

674
00:41:03.836 --> 00:41:05.629
[tense music playing]

675
00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:07.798
At that moment. I was thinking.

676
00:41:07.882 --> 00:41:09.133
"Don't do a double fault."

677
00:41:14.054 --> 00:41:14.889
[line] Fault!

678
00:41:14.972 --> 00:41:15.890
[Toni] <i>Double fault.</i>

679
00:41:18.184 --> 00:41:19.477
[umpire] Five-three.

680
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.479
The moment and the situation

681
00:41:21.562 --> 00:41:25.107
take their toll on me and I make mistakes.

682
00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:29.320
[Roger] <i>He knows that</i>
<i>two or three bad points on his serve</i>

683
00:41:29.403 --> 00:41:30.529
<i>can cost him the match.</i>

684
00:41:30.613 --> 00:41:34.116
And I think that stress
maybe manifested itself.

685
00:41:36.494 --> 00:41:38.496
[crowd cheering]

686
00:41:47.087 --> 00:41:49.965
There were too many missed opportunities.

687
00:41:50.549 --> 00:41:53.802
<i>Moments like these</i>
<i>are to Federer's advantage.</i>

688
00:42:11.487 --> 00:42:12.905
[commentator 1] <i>Stunning!</i>

689
00:42:14.114 --> 00:42:15.574
[umpire] Eight-seven. Nadal.

690
00:42:19.662 --> 00:42:22.248
[Toni] <i>I told Rafael.</i>
<i>"If you have a match point.</i>

691
00:42:22.331 --> 00:42:25.209
<i>serve to his backhand and charge the net.</i>

692
00:42:25.709 --> 00:42:27.253
<i>so you don't think so much."</i>

693
00:42:37.012 --> 00:42:38.389
[cheering erupts]

694
00:42:39.974 --> 00:42:41.100
[umpire] Eight all.

695
00:42:44.895 --> 00:42:47.481
Federer didn't follow my lead.
he didn't miss.

696
00:42:48.774 --> 00:42:50.985
[commentator 2] <i>Championship point's</i>
<i>gone for Nadal.</i>

697
00:42:58.367 --> 00:43:00.286
[umpire] Game. The fourth set.

698
00:43:01.662 --> 00:43:03.038
Two sets all.

699
00:43:03.539 --> 00:43:06.166
[commentator 1]
<i>Nadal has had his heart ripped out.</i>

700
00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:08.711
<i>He must feel absolutely hollow.</i>

701
00:43:09.503 --> 00:43:12.965
[Clarey] <i>Up two sets</i>
<i>and then losing the two breakers</i>

702
00:43:13.048 --> 00:43:16.385
certainly can make him
start to question things again.

703
00:43:16.885 --> 00:43:19.972
Like in 2007.
where he wasn't able to close.

704
00:43:20.055 --> 00:43:21.181
[thunder rumbling]

705
00:43:21.265 --> 00:43:24.101
[commentator 2] <i>The inevitable</i>
<i>has finally struck Center Court.</i>

706
00:43:24.184 --> 00:43:27.438
<i>This band of sort of dark clouds.</i>
<i>it finally produced some rain.</i>

707
00:43:27.521 --> 00:43:29.064
<i>but it has in thisâ€¦</i>

708
00:43:30.149 --> 00:43:31.609
<i>great exercise at Wimbledon.</i>

709
00:43:32.484 --> 00:43:35.613
[commentator 1]
<i>Back into the locker room once again.</i>

710
00:43:38.949 --> 00:43:40.743
[Toni] <i>When I got to the locker roomâ€¦</i>

711
00:43:42.745 --> 00:43:45.623
I thought. "Okay. Rafael will beâ€¦

712
00:43:46.665 --> 00:43:50.753
he will be very upset. right?
After having lost so many opportunities."

713
00:43:50.836 --> 00:43:52.504
[soft stoic music playing]

714
00:43:52.588 --> 00:43:53.797
[thunder cracking]

715
00:43:53.881 --> 00:43:56.759
[Toni] <i>And I thought.</i>
<i>"What can I say to cheer him up?"</i>

716
00:43:57.426 --> 00:43:58.469
<i>Andâ€¦</i>

717
00:43:59.053 --> 00:44:00.888
<i>I didn't have many ideas.</i>

718
00:44:06.560 --> 00:44:10.064
<i>And then. Rafael.</i>
<i>who was tying his shoes. said to me.</i>

719
00:44:12.232 --> 00:44:14.234
 "I think you can stop the rain."

720
00:44:14.818 --> 00:44:16.445
"I'm not going to lose."

721
00:44:17.571 --> 00:44:18.947
<i>"I'm not going to lose."</i>

722
00:44:21.784 --> 00:44:25.204
"He may beat me.
but I'm not going to lose. I'm not."

723
00:44:25.287 --> 00:44:28.791
"Mentally. I'm going to be 100%

724
00:44:29.291 --> 00:44:30.209
in every point."

725
00:44:30.959 --> 00:44:32.586
"I can't allow myself

726
00:44:33.712 --> 00:44:35.923
a single moment of weakness."

727
00:44:37.758 --> 00:44:41.428
<i>I was willing to suffer more than him.</i>

728
00:44:46.058 --> 00:44:47.935
[commentator 2]
<i>A brief rain shower has passed.</i>

729
00:44:48.018 --> 00:44:50.896
<i>We've got one more segment</i>

730
00:44:50.979 --> 00:44:54.900
<i>to see if there will be</i>
<i>a Wimbledon champion declared tonight.</i>

731
00:44:54.983 --> 00:44:56.985
[applause]

732
00:44:57.778 --> 00:45:01.573
[Toni] <i>And when I saw him</i>
<i>go back out on the court again.</i>

733
00:45:04.159 --> 00:45:05.536
<i>I knew he would win.</i>

734
00:45:06.036 --> 00:45:08.038
[music builds]

735
00:45:08.831 --> 00:45:13.627
[commentator 2] <i>Six and a half hours</i>
<i>of the entire exercise today.</i>

736
00:45:14.128 --> 00:45:16.422
[Clarey] <i>By that time. it was really dark.</i>

737
00:45:17.005 --> 00:45:19.466
And my screen on my laptop
was just glowing.

738
00:45:23.387 --> 00:45:25.139
<i>They should not have been playing tennis.</i>

739
00:45:27.182 --> 00:45:28.600
<i>But it was tremendous.</i>

740
00:45:28.684 --> 00:45:29.935
[music builds]

741
00:45:41.488 --> 00:45:42.906
[cheering]

742
00:45:42.990 --> 00:45:44.491
Come on!

743
00:45:44.575 --> 00:45:47.035
[inaudible]

744
00:45:49.580 --> 00:45:50.914
[cheering continues]

745
00:45:50.998 --> 00:45:53.417
[Rafa] <i>It was a tough match.</i>

746
00:45:56.128 --> 00:45:58.005
<i>And you couldn't see much.</i>

747
00:45:59.339 --> 00:46:01.133
<i>And I was at my limit.</i>

748
00:46:01.884 --> 00:46:05.679
<i>Just focused on trying</i>
<i>to keep giving myself opportunities.</i>

749
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:14.480
[Toni] <i>There's always</i>
<i>the temptation to give up.</i>

750
00:46:15.564 --> 00:46:19.026
<i>But when you get used</i>
<i>to enduring a little moreâ€¦</i>

751
00:46:19.109 --> 00:46:20.152
<i>"That one more ball."</i>

752
00:46:21.904 --> 00:46:23.655
<i>That's what great champions doâ€¦</i>

753
00:46:24.656 --> 00:46:26.825
<i>endure one more ball.</i>

754
00:46:29.912 --> 00:46:32.247
[commentator 2]
<i>A phenomenal get by Nadal here.</i>

755
00:46:32.748 --> 00:46:35.167
<i>Now he's got the championship point.</i>

756
00:46:37.252 --> 00:46:40.339
[Rafa] <i>I think Roger.</i>
<i>at that moment. was at his limit.</i>

757
00:46:42.174 --> 00:46:44.927
<i>"He's waiting for me</i>
<i>to serve to his backhand."</i>

758
00:46:45.594 --> 00:46:47.221
<i>"Maybe I could surprise him."</i>

759
00:46:48.972 --> 00:46:50.933
<i>There are no easy balls.</i>

760
00:46:53.018 --> 00:46:56.146
<i>I had given him a ball</i>
<i>where he had time to think.</i>

761
00:46:57.773 --> 00:47:00.484
<i>Sometimes it's easier</i>
<i>to hit without thinking.</i>

762
00:47:01.068 --> 00:47:03.070
[optimistic music playing]

763
00:47:18.627 --> 00:47:19.962
[thunder rumbling]

764
00:47:20.045 --> 00:47:22.881
[Rafa] <i>There's not only</i>
<i>one path to success.</i>

765
00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:29.680
<i>It's probably not necessary</i>
<i>to suffer the stress that I have suffered</i>

766
00:47:29.763 --> 00:47:32.182
<i>to become what I have become.</i>

767
00:47:34.852 --> 00:47:38.605
<i>But I followed the path</i>
<i>that Toni set for me.</i>

768
00:47:40.315 --> 00:47:43.151
<i>And I think it was the right path.</i>

769
00:47:44.319 --> 00:47:46.029
[triumphant music playing]

770
00:47:47.948 --> 00:47:50.200
[cheering continues]

771
00:47:59.126 --> 00:48:00.961
[umpire] Game. set. match. Nadal!

772
00:48:10.470 --> 00:48:12.806
[Rafa] <i>People thought that I was a winner.</i>

773
00:48:13.807 --> 00:48:15.309
<i>I'm not a winner.</i>

774
00:48:16.435 --> 00:48:17.936
<i>I'm a competitor.</i>

775
00:48:20.606 --> 00:48:21.648
<i>Victoryâ€¦</i>

776
00:48:23.358 --> 00:48:25.068
<i>lasts but a while.</i>

777
00:48:26.236 --> 00:48:27.237
<i>It's momentary.</i>

778
00:48:27.321 --> 00:48:28.906
WIMBLEDON CHAMPION
CONGRATULATIONS. RAFA!

779
00:48:30.365 --> 00:48:32.409
[Rafa] <i>What has always motivated me</i>

780
00:48:32.492 --> 00:48:35.120
<i>is the desire to keep fighting.</i>

781
00:48:37.456 --> 00:48:38.665
<i>'Cause the way I see it.</i>

782
00:48:38.749 --> 00:48:41.001
<i>satisfaction comes</i>
<i>from what's challenging</i>.

783
00:48:44.630 --> 00:48:46.632
[battle music playing]

784
00:49:03.190 --> 00:49:05.192
[music turns serene]

785
00:51:44.810 --> 00:51:46.603
[music fades]
